        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Job 34</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="1" xml:id="Job-034-001"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg001"
                                 /><supplied reason="lost">Da qaruv berdi Elihu da
                                ajtty.</supplied><anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg001"
                                 /><ref n="1" target="#Job-034-fn1" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="2" xml:id="Job-034-002">Tynlanyz uslular sözlerime da bilivčüler qulaq
                            salynyz mana.</l>
                        <l n="3" xml:id="Job-034-003">Ki qulaq sözlerni synajdyr da tanlaj tatuvun
                            ašnyn aladyr.</l>
                        <l n="4" xml:id="Job-034-004">Töreni synajyq özimizge bilejik aramyzda nedir
                            jaḥšy.</l>
                        <l n="5" xml:id="Job-034-005">Ki ajtty Ijov rast boldum da
                            <milestone unit="page" n="96v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            Tenri keterdi töremni.</l>
                        <l n="6" xml:id="Job-034-006">Karanjamny aldajmenmo syzlavludur oɣum
                            jazyqsyz.</l>
                        <l n="7" xml:id="Job-034-007">Kim jigit Ijov kibik ičer elikni suvnu
                            kibik.</l>
                        <l n="8" xml:id="Job-034-008">Da bardy qošulma qyluvčular byla avanlyq da
                            barma qynɣyrlyq el byla.</l>
                        <l n="9" xml:id="Job-034-009">Ki ajtty fajdaly bolmasty kiši jürügeninde
                            jolu byla Tenrinin.</l>
                        <l n="10" xml:id="Job-034-010">Anyn üčün aqylly el tynlanyz
                            <milestone unit="page" n="97r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            mana hašša bolɣaj Tenrige qynɣyrlyq etmekten da küčlü Tenrige
                            avanlyqtan.</l>
                        <l n="11" xml:id="Job-034-011">Ki išine köre adamnyn tölejdi anar da joluna
                            köre kišinin učratadyr anar.</l>
                        <l n="12" xml:id="Job-034-012">Ham kertiden Tenri qynɣyrlyq etmejdir da
                            küčlü Tenri qynɣyrajtmajdyr töreni.</l>
                        <l n="13" xml:id="Job-034-013">Kim bujurdu anar jaratma jerni <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg002" />kim symarlady anar
                                jerni<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg002" /><ref n="2"
                                target="#Job-034-fn2" type="noteAnchor" /> da kim qojdu dunjany
                            barčasyn.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="97v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="14" xml:id="Job-034-014">Eger qojsa anar fikirin tirligin da ǯanyn
                            özüne jyštyryr. <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg003" /><foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ופ׳ שני </foreign>
                            Eger qojsyjdy Tenri <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >וכו׳</foreign>
                            .<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg003" /><ref n="3"
                                target="#Job-034-fn3" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="15" xml:id="Job-034-015">Tynar bar ten birge da adam topraqqa qajtyr
                                <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg004" /><foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            tynɣajdy<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg004" /><ref n="4"
                                target="#Job-034-fn4" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="16" xml:id="Job-034-016">Da eger <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg005" />klejden ese<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Job--seg005" /><ref n="5" target="#Job-034-fn5"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> anlama tynlaɣyn bunu qulaq salɣyn avazyna
                            sözlerimnin.</l>
                        <l n="17" xml:id="Job-034-017">Muna ḥor etivčü töreni aɣalyq bolurmo jemese
                            küčlü cadiqni qynɣyr etelirmusen.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="98r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="18" xml:id="Job-034-018">Ajtylyrmo bijge bajbaq rašaʿ dep
                            ǯomartlarɣa.</l>
                        <l n="19" xml:id="Job-034-019">Ki jüz etmejdir jüzlerine aɣalyqlarnyn da
                            tanylmajdyr ǯomart alnynda jarlynyn ki iši qudratlarynyn barčaly.</l>
                        <l n="20" xml:id="Job-034-020">Köz jumčuɣuna ölediler da jarty kečede
                            alɣasandylar ulus da ašyp ketediler da ketediler klegi byla Tenrinin
                            tüvül qol byla.</l>
                        <l n="21" xml:id="Job-034-021">Ki ʿenajatlary jollary üstüne kišinin da bar
                            atlamlaryn köredir.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="98v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="22" xml:id="Job-034-022">Joḥtur qaranɣylyq da joḥtur tuman jašynma
                            anda avanlyq qyluvčularɣa.</l>
                        <l n="23" xml:id="Job-034-023">Ki qojmajdy kiši üstüne erksizlik barmaq üčün
                            Tenrige törege.</l>
                        <l n="24" xml:id="Job-034-024">Vatadyr küčlülerni tergevsiz da turɣuzadyr
                            özgelerni alar ornuna.</l>
                        <l n="25" xml:id="Job-034-025">Anyn üčün ki tanyjdyr išlerin alarnyn da
                            ajlandyradyr köče<ref n="6" target="#Job-034-fn6" type="noteAnchor" />
                            byla da jančyladyrlar.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="99r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="26" xml:id="Job-034-026">Ornunda rašaʿlarnyn vatadyr alarny ornunda
                            körüvčülernin.</l>
                        <l n="27" xml:id="Job-034-027">Anyn üčün ki kedergi kettiler artyndan da bar
                            jollaryn anlamadylar.</l>
                        <l n="28" xml:id="Job-034-028">Keltirme üstüne firjatyn jarlynyn da firjatyn
                            miskinlernin ešitedir.</l>
                        <l n="29" xml:id="Job-034-029">Da ol tynč etse da kim qozɣar da jašyrsa
                            qyblalaryn da kim baɣar any da ḥanlyq üstüne da adam üstüne birge.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="99v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="30" xml:id="Job-034-030">Bij bolmaɣy rašaʿ adamnyn jazyqlaryndandy
                            ulusnun.</l>
                        <l n="31" xml:id="Job-034-031">Ki Tenrige ušajdyr ajtma bošattym
                            čajpamamdyr.</l>
                        <l n="32" xml:id="Job-034-032">Neni bilmejmen sen üvretken mana eger avanlyq
                            qyldym ese arttyrmamen.</l>
                        <l n="33" xml:id="Job-034-033">Seninmo kleginden tügeller any neni sen ḥor
                            etesen ki sen <addSpan spanTo="#Job-034-add001" /><addSpan
                                spanTo="#Job-034-add001" />b<anchor xml:id="Job-034-add001"
                                type="addSpan" /><anchor xml:id="Job-034-add002" type="addSpan" />
                            sajlaɣyn tüvül men da ne bilesen sözlegin.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="100r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="34" xml:id="Job-034-034">Aqylly el ajtyrlar menim üčün da uslu kiši
                            tynlavču meni.</l>
                        <l n="35" xml:id="Job-034-035">Ijov aqyl byla tüvül sözlejdi sözleri us byla
                            tüvül.</l>
                        <l n="36" xml:id="Job-034-036">Klegim ki synalɣaj Ijov emirgedejin qaruv
                            qajtarɣanlary üčün avančy el byla <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg006" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            qajtarɣany üčün qaruvlaryn avančy elnin<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Job--seg006" /><ref n="7" target="#Job-034-fn7"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="37" xml:id="Job-034-037">Ki arttyradyr jazyɣy üstüne güneḥ aramyzda
                            uvuč qaɣady da arttyrady ajtmaqlaryn Tenrige.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 34:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן
                                אֱלִיהוּא וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 34:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Elihu
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>kim bujurdu anar jaratma jerni</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">מִי־פָקַד עָלָיו
                                אָרְצָה </foreign>
                            ‘who gave him charge over the earth’. | C: <emph>kim saɣyndy üstünä
                                jerni</emph>. | QB: <emph>kim saɣyndy üstünä jerni</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>kim bujurdu anar jaratma jerni</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>kim qajtardy anyn erkińa jerni</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn3" type="footnote">An alternative translation of Job
                            34:14, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ופ׳ שני </foreign>
                            ‘and a second interpretation’. The Hebrew abbreviation <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וכו׳ </foreign>
                            stands for <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְכֻלֵּה </foreign>
                            ~ <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְכֻלֵּיהּ </foreign>
                            ~ <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְכֻלְהוּ </foreign>
                            ‘and so forth’. The abbreviation <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ופ׳ </foreign>
                            stands for <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וּפְשָׁט </foreign>
                            ‘and an interpretation’. | C: <emph>Egär qojsa aŋar köŋlin ǯanyn da
                                näfäsin özünä čöplär</emph>. | QB: <emph>Egär qojsa aŋar köŋlin
                                ǯanyn da näfäsin özünä čöplär</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>Eger
                                qojsa anar fikirin tirligin da ʒanyn özüne jystyryr</emph>. |
                            Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>Eger qajyrsejdyr anar fikirin ǯanyn da nafstyn
                                öźuńa ištyrsejdyr</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn4" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>tynar</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">אִם־יָשִׂים </foreign>
                            ‘if he should set’, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>qorar</emph>. | QB: <emph>qorar</emph>. | ADub.III.84:
                                <emph>tynar</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                            <emph>tynhejdyr</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn5" type="footnote">An erroneous continuative present
                            form, instead of <emph>klejdesen</emph> &amp;lt; <emph>klejdyr
                                esen</emph>. | C: deest. | QB: deest. | ADub.III.84: <emph>klejde
                                esen</emph>; an erroneous continuative present form, instead of
                                <emph>klejdesen</emph> &amp;lt; <emph>klejdyr esen</emph>. |
                            Kobeckaitė (2019): deest.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn6" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>keče</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-034-fn7" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>qaruv qajtarɣanlary üčün avančy el byla</emph>, the equivalent
                            of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >עַל־תְּשֻׁבֹת בְּאַנְשֵׁי־אָוֶן </foreign>
                            ‘because he answers like wicked men’, written after Heb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>tešuvalar učun kišilärinä jalɣančylyqnyŋ</emph>. | QB:
                                <emph>tešuvalar učun kišilärinä jalɣančylyqnyŋ</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>qajtarɣany ücün qaruvlaryn avancy elnin</emph>
                            <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            <emph>qaruv qajtarɣanlary ücün avancy el byla</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>qaruv qajtarmaḥlar üč́uń qynhyr eĺ byla</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
